         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Office of Lands and Survey, ¶ Melbourne, 28th November, 1868. ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ In acknowledgment of your communication of 27th ultimo, ¶ name in full.M to J. Grant, 27 October 1868.I do not understand what...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">68.11.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James Grant</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">R68/17158, unit 750, VPRS 44/P inward registered and unregistered correspondence, VA 538 Department of Crown Lands and Survey, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Office of Lands and Survey,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, 28th November, 1868.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In acknowledgment of your communication of 27th ultimo,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; background-color: #FFFF00; ">name in full.</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #00FF00; ">M to J. Grant, 27 October 1868.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; background-color: #FFFF00; ">I do not understand what name is being sought&gt;</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; background-color: #00FF00; ">In principle we don't need to give this, While I recognize the usage is no longer well</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; background-color: #00FF00; ">understood, I'm a bit reluctant to loss it</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>urging your exemption from payment of Ferry charges at Jolimont, whilst in the execution of Official garden duty, I beg to state that all Government Officials, including members of the Board of Land and Works, pay when they cross ferries, the ordinary fares charged by the licensed ferryman</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your most obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">[...]</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">IF this represents an illegible signature it is probably Hodgkinson, who replied with this valediction in many cases, Others are for Asst Comm of L &amp; S, If there is a blank, then I guess that the item is from a copy book</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>See also my comments under n 1 of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">27</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">-10-68.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[for] Commissioner of Lands and Survey</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Government Botanist,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>&amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M responded in a minute dated 3 December: 'I beg respectfully to draw attention to the circumstance, that the ferry from which exception of fare for the botanic establishment (and of course also members of the board of Land &amp; Works) is sought, has its buildings within the area under the control of myself on behalf of the Board of Land and Works, so that perhaps an apt recognition of authority over the ferry might be favorably considered on the occasion when the tender is to be renewed. Then also perhaps it might be advantageous to introduce a clause into the tender, by which the Director of the botanic Garden on behalf of the Board of Land &amp; Works would be authorized, to give such orders to the ferryman, as might at any time be imperative for the preservation of order and for the safety and the convenience of the public. An augmentation of the rent might also perhaps be deemed right by the Board.'</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">MS annotation</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">:</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>no decision 15.12.68 Sch: 68/51'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Does this refer to Board Minutes?</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">That is a possible interpretation,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">so looked into 1869 letters</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">, but nothing specifically on this point being notified to M, However M did not give up easily, so the text below added as an extension of this note.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1015FA; ">M persisted in his attempt to get free passage by support</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1015FA; ">ing<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1015FA; ">an additional ferry,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1015FA; ">to avoid a monopoly not<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1015FA; ">run by<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1015FA; ">the existing ferryman</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1015FA; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1015FA; ">Brandon</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1015FA; ">, with a provision that members and officers of the Board of Lands and Works and Garden staff be exempt when using it on public duty (M to C. Hodgkinson,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1015FA; ">18 February 1869). Later, in M to C. Hodgkinson, 30 Jun 1869, he drew attention to the cheap rent that Brandon had enjoyed since the floods of 1863.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
